STEP 2: FIRESTORE DATABASE STRUCTURE
We keep it clean and scalable.
You will have TWO main collections:
users (collection)
Each document ID = user UID from Firebase Auth
Structure:
users
└── userUID
├── fullName: string
├── businessName: string
├── phone: string
├── createdAt: timestamp
Example:
users └── AbC123UID fullName: "Anas Garba" businessName: "Anas Electronics" phone: "080xxxxxxx" createdAt: 2026-03-02

 receipts (collection)
Each document = one transaction
Structure:
receipts
└── receiptID (auto generated or custom ID) ├── merchantId: userUID ├── businessName: string ├── customerName: string ├── itemDescription: string ├── amount: number ├── date: timestamp ├── receiptCode: string (unique short ID) ├── createdAt: timestamp
Example:
receipts └── xYz789 merchantId: AbC123UID businessName: "Anas Electronics" customerName: "Musa" itemDescription: "Phone Charger" amount: 4500 date: 2026-03-02 receiptCode: "TPL-83921" createdAt: timestamp

IMPORTANT
receiptCode is what customers will use to verify.
Example format generator:
TPL + random 5 digits
Example: TPL-48291
That is what appears on receipt + QR code.

